Euroviisut 2007 was the show in which Finland chose its entry for the Eurovision Song Contest 2007. Finland hosted the Eurovision Song Contest for the first time, after Lordi won in 2006.

Each participant sang two songs in their respective semifinals, and televoting selected the best song of the two to be sung by that artist in the final. In the final, the top three songs from the televoting were performed again, with another televote to select the winner. 

Hanna Pakarinen won Euroviisut 2007 on 17 February with her song "", and she represented Finland at the Eurovision Song Contest 2007 where she came 17th with 53 points.





      



      



      



      









